issue.title: Outdated changelog
issue.body:
<!---
BEFORE YOU SUBMIT please search open/closed issues since someone might have asked the same thing before!

For feature requests see: https://feedback.neo4j.com/browser
-->

### Description
Clicking on the link to changelog in neo4j-browser shows an outdated wiki page

### Reproduce Steps
- Go to `About Neo4j ` and look for words "You are running"
- Click on "Changelog"

![image](https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j-browser/assets/6624639/ca35b9a2-6df0-4f4b-84d3-43106a76bc56)


### Expected Behavior
- Changelog up to date (here for version 5.12.0)

### Current Behavior
- 2-years old changelog

![image](https://github.com/neo4j/neo4j-browser/assets/6624639/a9b84071-d313-406d-bec6-2470b1d37e40)


### What needs to be done to address this issue? Ideally, provide a pull request with a fix.
Update the old changelog or change the link to an up-to-date document.

### Your Environment
Running on Neo Desktop for Mac (latest everything)

issue.title: Datetime function timezone issue when hour is 00
issue.body:
### Description  
The `datetime()` function appears to have an error when the time is between 12-1am. This does not happen everywhere, however, as it works as expected when using cypher-shell.

### Reproduce Steps  
Run a query trying to use `datetime()` to convert a time between midnight and 1:00am.

#### Expected Behavior  
With 1:00 am, the time zone returns as expected (-04:00): 
```lang-cypher
RETURN datetime('2023-05-30T01:00:00[America/New_York]')
// Expected: 2023-05-30T01:00:00-04:00[America/New_York]
// Actual:   2023-05-30T01:00:00-04:00[America/New_York]
```

#### Current Behavior
With anything in the 12:00am range, the time zone changes to +20:00:
```lang-cypher
RETURN datetime('2023-05-30T00:59:00[America/New_York]')
// Expected: 2023-05-30T00:59:00-04:00[America/New_York]
// Actual:   2023-05-30T00:59:00+20:00[America/New_York]
```

This happens when passing the individual components, too, and only happens with 12-1am. I've tried with several different years and days.
```lang-cypher
UNWIND range(0, 23) AS hr
RETURN datetime({year:2023, month:5, day:30, hour:hr, minute:0, second:0, timezone:'America/New_York'})
// All correct expect the first hour of the day.
```

# Environment information
- Database v5.8.0, Neo4j desktop client v1.5.7 on Windows 11
- Ran this in the Neo4j Browser to isolate the problem. It works when I run it in the Neo4j Terminal.
